This paper deals with the optimization problem of dependency solving in Linux package managers, which involves finding the best combination of packages to install while satisfying dependencies and avoiding conflicts. This problem is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) as it requires efficient algorithms to search through the space of possible solutions. Additionally, it involves programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with package management systems. Finally, the paper compares different solvers based on their performance, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
